Title: Sending and Receiving GMail Email Attachments that contain Code or Binaries
Description: As a developer, you're likely to occasionally send an email with attachments that are either code or binary executable files either as straight files or in a zipped up collection of code or binary files. You'll find that you can't actually send certain types of files or even files embedded in archives and even encrypted archives as most mail servers these days scan file content both before sending and when receiving email. In this post I discuss what works and what doesn't and how you can work around those files that don't work. It ain't pretty...

Title: Uno Platform for Figma Preview 5: Enhanced Features for Designers and Developers
Description: Uno Platform has released Preview 5 of its Figma plugin, offering enhanced features for designers and developers. The latest version of the plugin allows the creation of custom colors, enables the import of Design Systems Packages (DSP), and offers new controls such as Pips Pager, TabBar, and ItemsRepeater for greater flexibility in creating dynamic designs.

Title: How to lock orientation at runtime on iOS 16 with .NET MAUI and Xamarin.Forms
Description: With iOS 16, Apple made some old APIs non-functional. This includes also the established way of locking the orientation. In this post, I am going to show you how you can lock orientation on iOS 16 while the app is running with both .NET MAUI and Xamarin.Forms.
